Quote:  The lucerne-fed ewes wintered well so far as feeding of dry lucerne was concerned, but foot-scald caused a great deal of trouble, and the ewes had to be moved to other pastures from time to time. On the grass-only area no difficulties were encountered, either from foot-scald or at lambing.
